She then had two days of minimal symptoms, but on 1/21 experienced sudden swelling of her left arm at the shot site with rapid expansion of the rash. The rash was itchy and the arm was painful. She had a significant headache, fatigue, and temperature to 99.3 F.  These symptoms worsened over the next two days, with temperatures reaching 100 degrees F, continued headache, fatigue, and increased arm swelling.  On 1/23/2021 the arm began to improve, but fevers to 99.3, fatigue and headaches continued.  The rash had expanded to almost 12 cm x 6 cm. Tylenol 500 mg dosing was used for symptom control with some improvement.  By 1/26/2021 the rash had mostly disappeared, the headache was gone, fevers were gone, and the fatigue remained. In all, symptoms lasted 12 days post-vaccination.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: About 5-10 min after injection, I started to feel a little bit shaky and I felt my heart rate  had increased a lot. I just did not feel myself, out of sorts. They had me come to the ambulance to monitor me for a bit longer.  Around the injection site I had a large ring of hives, it was red and quite warm. I was red and warm also on my neck and somewhat on the top of my back. They hooked me up to EKG, took my blood pressure, pulse ox and heart rate again,  BP and heart rate were still high, O2 sats were normal,  but I was feeling better. We waited 15 minutes approximately and they checked my vitals again and my blood pressure has down, as well as my heart rate. So they felt it was OK to discharge me with instructions to take an antihistamine when I got home,  and to call emergency services if I needed further help.  My symptoms all subsided completely and I was fine at home.

Pain lasted for 3-4 hours. Initially it was severe, pulsating, acute pain as if nerve pressing against chest. Unbearable pain. I was unable to lie down, turn on sides. Pain would aggravate on movements and if I would touch the specific spot in my chest. . Deep breaths reduced the pain to some extent. Pain severity decreased after 4 hours after which I started getting pain in my left arm, radiating to my pinky finger.  The pain also  radiates to left upper back on movements and exerting left arm for long time, especially typing computer keyboard, doing daily chores cooking, washing dirty dishes, sleeping on the side. ,I am unable to sleep on the left side, if I sleep on left side, I start getting tingling and numbness in my left arm. I did not take any pain medications until Jan 26th as the pain did not disappear. Once at night the pain also radiated to my left leg , I felt  numbness when I tried to sleep on my left side. Occasionally, I feel pain in my right arm and right back. The pain near the sternum area reduced significantly when I took two doses of Ibuprofen 600 on Jan 26th in the afternoon and night. The pain in left arm radiating towards left pinky still persists, with numbness and tingling  if I do daily task for longer duration. Ibuprofen helps to relieve pain temporarily. weakness and fallsNarrative:  95 yo male w/ a PMH significant for Afib, legal blindness, Hx of CVA, cognitive impairment, GERD, HTN, pseudogout, BPH, chronic knee infection, and DJD who received his first dose of the Moderna COVID-19 vaccine on 01/08/21. The pt's COVID-19  screening questionnaire prior to receiving the vaccine was negative. The pt presented to the ED on 01/13/21 for weakness and m  PCR test on ultiple recent falls (since receiving his first dose of the COVID-19 vaccine). The pt's COVID-19 01/13/20  was positive and he was admitted. He was started on treatment with remdesivir + dexamethasone on 1/14. The pt initially required supplemental oxygen via low-flow NC, however his oxygen requirements increased to 100% NRB. On 01/16/21 his MPOA elected for hospice care.  The pt passed on 01/17/21. Unclear if the COVID-19 vaccine attributed to the patient's hospitalization and eventual death, or whether these events occurred from COVID-19 itself, however this case is being reported the FDA since this vaccine is under an emergency use authorization (EUA).

right arm weakness; right arm pain /  increased pain with swimming / arm pain escalated to sharp shooting pain; arm pain and weakness has left her unable to swim; This case was reported by a nurse via call center representative and described the occurrence of weakness of arms in a 17-year-old female patient who received Men B NVS (Bexsero) (batch number ABXB09AZ, expiry date 31st March 2022) for prophylaxis. This report is made by GSK without prejudice and does not imply any admission or liability for the incident or its consequences.  Additional details were provided as follows: The patient received her first dose of Bexsero in the right deltoid. Immediately following the injection the patient complained of right arm pain. SYMPTOM_TEXT: face was still red; swollen; feeling weak; Tired; Severe allergic reaction; Difficulty swallowing; A spontaneous report was received from a healthcare professional concerning herself, a 28 year old female patient, who received Moderna's COVID-19 Vaccine (mRNA-1273) and experienced a severe allergic reaction,  difficulty swallowing, face was still red, swollen, felt  week and tired.  The patient's medical history included anxiety and allergy to latex. Concomitant product use was not provided by the reporter.   On 12-Jan-2021, 15 minutes prior to the onset of the symptoms, the patient received one of two planned doses of mRNA-1273 (026L20A) intramuscularly in an unknown injection site for prophylaxis of COVID-19 infection.   12-Jan-2021, after receiving the vaccine, the patient experienced a severe allergic reaction which made her face puffy, red, and covered with hives.  She took 50 mg of diphenhydramine.  She was also having trouble pronouncing words because her tongue was swelling and she couldn't swallow water, so she used epinephrine  and go to the emergency room.  On 14 Jan 2021 she felt weak and tired.   On 13 Jan 2021follow up information was received and per source document/call -  In addition one day later, on 13Jan2021 around 5:30 pm, patient reported that she went to the bathroom and noticed that her "face was still red" and "swollen" and had a "little bit of difficulty swallowing" and took another unknown dose of Benadryl and felt better.   Action taken with mRNA-1273 in response to the events was not provided.   The outcome of the events,severe allergic reaction, difficulty swallowing, face was still red, swollen and felt weak and tired was not reported.; Reporter's Comments: This case concerns a 28 year old female with medical history of anxiety and allergy to latex who experienced serious medically significant unlisted event of severe allergic reaction described as her face puffy, red, covered with hives, tongue swelling and difficulty swallowing within 15 minutes after the first dose of the study medication administration (LOT:026L20A). Patient also experienced additional reported events of non-serious listed events of "face was still red" and "feeling tired" and non-serious unlisted events of "face swollen", had a "little bit of difficulty swallowing", and "feeling weak". Patient was treated for the severe allergic reaction with initially Benadryl 50 mg and then with epinephrine pen and was sent to ER. Based on the temporal association between the use of the product and the start date of the events within 15 minutes of receiving the vaccine, a causal relationship cannot be excluded and the event of severe allergic reaction is possibly related to vaccine. Additional reported events of non-serious listed events of "face was still red" and "feeling tired" and non-serious unlisted events of "face swollen", had a "little bit of difficulty swallowing" and "feeling weak" are possibly related to vaccine.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Acute pancreatitis; Acute renal failure; Low blood pressure; Weakness; Decreased appetite; Fatigue; Alanine aminotransferase increased; Aspartate aminotransferase increased; Troponin increased; Lipase increased; Blood bilirubin increased; A spontaneous report was received from a physician concerning an 81-year-old, male patient who received Moderna's COVID-19 vaccine (mRNA-1273) and developed an odd presentation of acute pancreatitis, acute renal failure, low blood pressure, weakness, decreased appetite and fatigue.  The patient's medical history included advanced dementia, heart disease, pulmonary embolism and possible leukemia. Concomitant product use was not provided by the reporter.  On 05 Jan 2021, prior to the onset of the events, the patient received their first of two planned doses of mRNA-1273 for prophylaxis of COVID-19 infection.   On 08 Jan 2021, three days after vaccination, the patient developed symptoms of weakness, decreased appetite, and fatigue.   On 11 Jan 2021, the patient was admitted into the hospital with a diagnosis of low blood pressure,acute renal failure,acute pancreatitis,alanine aminotransferase increased,aspartate aminotransferase increased, troponin increased,lipase increased and blood bilirubin increased. Abnormal lab results included "significantly elevated" aspartate transaminase, alanine transaminase, bilirubin, lipase up to 1900, and "slightly elevated" troponin of 0.079.  On 13 Jan 2021, the patient's symptoms had improved, and he was discharged. Treatment for the event included two liters of intravenous fluid and supportive care.   Action taken with the second dose of mRNA-1273 in response to the event was not provided.    The events, acute pancreatitis, acute renal failure, low blood pressure, weakness, decreased appetite and fatigue, were considered resolved on 13 Jan 2021.   The physician assessed the events, acute pancreatitis, acute renal failure, low blood pressure, weakness, decreased appetite and fatigue, as not related to mRNA-1273. The physician's rationale was that the patient may have had a gallstone obstructing the pancreatic duct and once the stone passed, the patient got better with supportive care and slow administration of fluids.; Reporter's Comments: This case concerns a 81-year-old male patient with medical history of dementia, heart disease, pulmonary embolism, and possible leukemia, who received their first of two planned doses of mRNA-1273 (Lot unknown), and who experienced the serious unlisted events of acute pancreatitis, acute renal failure, low blood pressure, the non-serious listed event of fatigue, and the non-serious unlisted events of weakness, decreased appetite, elevated aspartate transaminase, elevated alanine transaminase, elevated bilirubin, elevated lipase, and elevated troponin.  Very limited information regarding these events has been provided at this time.  Based on the current available information and in agreement with the physician reporter's assessment, the events are assessed as unlikely related to mRNA-1273, noting the rapid improvement after administration of IV fluids.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Anaphylaxis-like symptoms; A spontaneous report was received from a physician concerning a 45-year-old,  patient who received Moderna's COVID-19 vaccine (mRNA-1273) and experienced anaphylaxis-like symptoms.  The patient's medical history included hypertension. The patient had no history of allergies or prior vaccine reactions. No concomitant medications were reported.  On 13 Jan 2021, the patient received their first of two planned doses of mRNA-1273 (Lot number: 041L20A) intramuscularly for prophylaxis of COVID-19 infection.  On 13 Jan 2021, the patient experienced anaphylaxis-like symptoms that included, anaphylaxis, angioedema, shortness of breath, itching, swelling of eyes, and sleepiness. The patient was treated with epinephrine injections and taken to the emergency department.  Action taken with mRNA-1273 in response to the event was not reported.  The outcome of the event, anaphylaxis-like symptoms, was unknown.; Reporter's Comments: This case concerns a 45-year-old patient with medical history of hypertension, who experienced a serious, unexpected event of Anaphylactoid reaction. The event occurred the day  the patient received the first dose of mRNA-1273 (Lot number: 041L20A), at an unspecified time. Based on the current available information and temporal association between the use of the product and the start date of the event, a causal relationship cannot be excluded.

Arm tenderness; Runny nose; Cough; Anaphylactic reaction; A spontaneous report was received from a 63-year-old male who received Moderna's COVID-19 vaccine and experienced anaphylactic reaction, arm tenderness, runny nose and cough.  The patient's medical history was not provided. No relevant concomitant medications were reported.   On 06 Jan 2021, prior to the onset of the events, the patient received their first of two planned doses of mRNA-1273 (Lot number:011(J/5)20A) intramuscularly in the left arm for prophylaxis of COVID-19 infection.   On 12 Jan 2021, patient started to experienced cough which got progressively worse, runny nose and his heart started racing. He could not swallow water, his airway was shutting down, and he stated that it was an anaphylactic reaction. Patient also felt exhausted with arm tenderness and pronounced discomfort. Treatment for the events were not provided.  Action taken with the second dose of mRNA-1273 in response to the event was not reported.   The outcome for the events, anaphylactic reaction, arm tenderness, runny nose and cough was unknown.; Reporter's Comments: This case concerns a 63-year-old, male patient, who experienced a serious unexpected event of anaphylactic reaction, and non-serious unexpected event of cough, and rhinorrhea, and a non-serious expected event of pain in extremity. The events occurred 1 day (same day) after first dose of mRNA-1273, lot # 011(J/5)20A. No treatment was administered. Based on the current available information and temporal association between the use of the product and onset of the events a causal relationship cannot be excluded.
HISTORY: Medical History/Concurrent Conditions: No adverse event (No medical history reported.)

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Low kidney function; A spontaneous report was received from a consumer who was also a 79-year-old, female patient who received Moderna's COVID-19 Vaccine (mRNA-1273) and experienced low kidney function.  The patient's medical history reported include rheumatoid arthritis, and infection. Concomitant medications include medications (unspecified) for rheumatoid arthritis, and antibiotics for infection.  On 06 Jan 2021, the patient received their first of two planned doses of mRNA-1273 (Lot number: 025L204A) for prophylaxis of COVID-19 infection.   On an undisclosed date in Jan 2021, the patient's kidney function was low. She reported that her doctor said it was nothing to worry about.  Treatment for the event was not reported.   Action taken with mRNA-1273 in response to the event was not provided.  The outcome of the event, low kidney function, was unknown.; Reporter's Comments: This case concerns a 79-year-old, female patient with medical history of rheumatoid arthritis and infection, who experienced an unexpected event of Renal impairment. The event occurred at an unspecified duration after the first dose of mRNA-1273 (Lot number: 025L204A). The patient was taking unspecified antibiotics for unspecified infection. Very limited information regarding this event has been provided at this time.  Based on temporal association between the use of the product and the start  of the event, a causal relationship cannot be excluded.

Knot on his arm; Vaccine subcutaneously injected; A spontaneous report was received from a male patient who received Moderna's COVID-19 Vaccine (mRNA-1273) and experienced knot on his arm and vaccine subcutaneously injected.   The patient's medical history was not provided. Concomitant product use was not provided by the reporter.   On 11 Jan 2021, the patient received their first of two planned doses of mRNA-1273 subcutaneously in the left deltoid for prophylaxis of COVID-19 infection.   On 11 Jan 2021, during vaccine administration, the patient was given the vaccine subcutaneously and he later noticed a knot on his arm. Treatment information was not provided.   Action taken with mRNA-1273 in response to the event was not provided.   The outcome of the event, vaccine subcutaneously injected, was considered resolved on 11 Jan 2021. The outcome of the event, knot on his arm, was not reported.; Reporter's Comments: This report refers to a case of a male patient who experienced non-serious event of mRNA-1273 vaccine was given subcutaneously (Vaccine given subcutaneously ,Vaccine administered at inappropriate site) and event of experienced knot on his arm (lot # unknown, Expiration date-unknown). The event of experienced knot on his arm is temporarily associated with the administration of mRNA-1273 vaccine, hence a causal association cannot be excluded. The event of vaccine given subcutaneously is considered not applicable
HISTORY: Medical History/Concurrent Conditions: No adverse event (No reported medical history)

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Administered vials that were exposed to room temperature for more than 12 hours; A spontaneous report was received from an employee and a physician concerning a patient, who received Moderna's COVID-19 vaccine (mRNA-1273) and was administered with product that was exposed to room temperature for more than twelve hours.   The patient's medical history was not provided. No relevant concomitant medications were reported.   On 04 Jan 2021, a freezer containing a vial of mRNA-1273 failed.  At 1:11 A.M. the vial experienced a temperature excursion, exceeding 8 degrees Celsius. Over time the dose thawed and reached room temperature.  On 04 Jan 2021, the patient received their first of two planned doses of mRNA-1273 intramuscularly for prophylaxis of COVID-19 infection and was administered with product that was exposed to room temperature for more than twelve hours.  No treatment information was provided.  Action taken with mRNA-1273 in response to the event was not reported.   The event, administered with product that was exposed to room  temperature for more than twelve hours, was resolved on 04 Jan 2021.; Reporter's Comments: This case concerns a patient of unknown gender and age who received their first of two planned doses of mRNA-1273 (Lot unknown), reporting Product that was exposed to room temperature for more than twelve hours without any associated adverse events.
HISTORY: Medical History/Concurrent Conditions: No adverse event (No medical history reported)

SYMPTOM_TEXT: like a slight paralysis; stiffness in the face; numbness in the face; A spontaneous report was received from a 64-year-old, male patient, who received Moderna's COVID-19 vaccine (mRNA-1273) and experienced like a slight paralysis, stiffness in the face and numbness in the face.   The patient's medical history, as reported, included high blood pressure. Concomitant medications reported included losartan.   On 13 Jan 2021, about 5 minutes prior to the onset of the events, the patient received their first of two planned doses of mRNA-1273 intramuscularly in the left arm for prophylaxis of COVID-19 infection.   On 13 Jan 2021, about 5 minutes after getting the Moderna COVID-19 vaccine, the patient experienced a stiffness and numbness in the face, like a slight paralysis. It started in the nose and spread out to the eyes and forehead. After about half an hour, he still experienced it a little bit. No medications were taken for the events.  Action taken with mRNA-1273 in response to the events was not reported.   The outcome of the events, like a slight paralysis, stiffness in the face and numbness in the face, was recovering/resolving.; Reporter's Comments: This spontaneous report refers to a case of a 64-year-old, male patient with medical history of high blood pressure who experienced a serious event slight paralysis and non-serious events of stiffness in the face and numbness in the face.  The events occurred 5 minutes after the administration of the mRNA-1273 vaccine (lot # unknown, expiration date-unknown). No treatment was administered, and patient is recovering. Based on the information provided which includes a temporal association, a causal association cannot be excluded.

she has pulled some of the vials that were used out of the sharps container and peeled off the label to find that the dots and lines disappeared. A female patient of an unspecified age received BNT162B2 (PFIZER-BIONTECH COVID-19 VACCINE, solution for injection, lot number: EK9231, expiry date: unknown, NDC number: 59267- 1000-1 ) via an unspecified route of administration, on an unspecified date, at 30mg/0.3mL, single for COVID-19 immunization. The patient's medical history and concomitant medications were not reported. The pharmacist reported that she has multiple vials of the COVID-19 vaccine that have either dots or fixed lines on the vials, presumably what could be a potential crack in the vial. The vials were all smooth on the outside. There are no particles and the vaccine looks normal, even after its been reconstituted. She pulled some of the vials that were used out of the sharps container and peeled off the label to find that the dots and lines disappeared. She felt that they may be a result of air trapped between the label and the vial but she states that she is not sure and would like to know if she can still use the product or should discard them. In follow-up the pharmacist reported seeing something strange in the vial after reconstituting it with the diluent. She noticed what looks like a core as she injected the syringe and on further injection, she noticed that the piece was reflecting and picking up light and this piece was not moving in the solution. And she added that there are 2 vials with this appearance, and they have the same LOT#.  Pharmacist stated, they didn't inject the vial into the patient.  Pharmacist stated, "It is not floating, it is a fixed spot on the vial where, when I look from one angle it looks like there could potentially be a core. So, it shows almost grey. When I move the vial, I can see the reflected light within the particle slightly and then if I move the vial further over where there is no fluid covering the spot, the spot is not noticeable. One vial is one spot, the other vial is a spot and what looks almost to be scraped on the inside. It is grey in color until I move the vial as such to where there is no fluid covering it, then it disappears. And when I move the vial further when there is fluid covering it, it will reflect light, so it's not really a true like particles, it's hard to describe. It is very, very small in 1 vial, may be the size like of a, I don't know like similar to like a 21 gauge needle. And then on the other vial it is one spot that's larger than that almost like the end of paper clip and then the part that almost appears to be like 'dry are faded' (voice distortion) and those are very, very faint lines. This happened after dilution of the vial with Sodium Chloride. I did not notice this prior to, I inspected the vial prior to dilution and I did not notice that either. At this point I completed the dilution around 8:55 for one of the vials and 9 o' clock for the other so.  It has been at as far as I am aware I have access to our continual monitor but we do keep a paper log of the refrigerator temp every day and it has been under refrigeration. It was removed from the ultra-low freezer at 8 o' clock on 11th, on Monday."   Follow-up (13Jan2021): New information received from a contactable pharmacist includes: clinical course and confirmed they didn't inject the vial into the patient. Sodium Chloride added as suspect drug.

The patient experienced feeling unwell on 10Jan2021; blood in urine on 10Jan2021 at 17:00; nausea at 10:00, chills at 11:00, almost passed out at doctor's office at 10:00, felt cold - all on 11Jan2021; getting really tired/fatigue on 14Jan2021 at 09:30; gets really sweaty on 13Jan2021 at 10:00; and dizziness on unknown date. The patient had the first shot on Friday (08Jan2021). On Sunday (10Jan2021), she started feeling bad. She was feeling good about getting it and had no reaction. She has an autoimmune disorder that made her a little afraid to take, but with all the indications, they said it would be much better for her to take it than to get the COVID virus. Sunday (10Jan2021), she does not feel good. So, she started having blood in urine. She thought she had a UTI and had not had one in 20 years. It felt like that is what she had and with the blood in urine. She just took Tylenol and waited until Monday morning because she does not like sitting in doctor's office. They gave her a cup to give sample and said she didn't need to see provider. They will have it checked and in the meantime call in a prescription. It kept getting worse and worse. She was about to passed out in the doctor's office on 11Jan2021, she got nauseous and almost threw up. She got in the car with her husband and he was trying to get her home. She got chills and got so cold and could not warm her body up. Her husband gave her Phenergan and it kind of knocked her out for a while to ease her nausea. She was thinking of going later today (14Jan2021), when she gets enough energy, to get a COVID test. She does not know if it will give false positive or not. She had chills and now she gets sweaty since 13Jan2021. She took her temperature and she did not have one. She just now got up. It is 10:00. She got up this morning (14Jan2021) and was really tired. She was not sweating this morning. Tiredness is kind of new, and when she talked to the nurse, she sort of felt like maybe it was a reaction to the COVID vaccine, but then she talked to her daughter and she said the symptoms she was having are usually symptoms that occur with second dose of the vaccine. It is not uncommon for people to have symptoms she was having. She wanted to know if she should have a COVID test. If she has had just one shot, would the test give a false positive coming from the COVID. They were asking if patient should take the second dose, and should she continue her UTI medication. Doctor's visit to give urine sample on 11Jan2021 (results: negative for UTI). She did not see a doctor though. They sent sample and prescribed a sulfa based medication for a UTI. She did start feeling a little better and stopped having blood in her urine. She plans to continue it because she does not like to stop taking an antibiotic. She did not have any clue that it was not a UTI until the nurse from her provider's office called to tell her results of urine sample was negative. Outcome of event getting really tired/fatigue was not recovered; events almost passed out at doctor's office, blood in urine, chills, and gets really sweaty was recovering; and unknown for other events.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Back pain; tired; whole body trembled; nervous; facial tingling; immediate pain in arm from injection; couldn't lift her arm at all; left eye twitching; Chills; Nausea; no appetite; whole body ache; This is a spontaneous report from a contactable consumer reporting for herself. A 68-year-old female patient received the first dose of bnt162b2 (BNT162B2, lot number and expiry date were not reported), via an unspecified route of administration, on 11Jan2021 5:15 PM at a single dose on arm for COVID-19 immunization. Medical history included ongoing shellfish allergy from 1975 (she carries epi pen), ongoing iodine allergy from 1975 (she carries epi pen), ongoing Mitral valve prolapse (for 20 years), blood pressure high, and cholesterol. The patient had mitral valve prolapse for about 20 years now. They are just watching it now. She just saw the cardiologist, and had an echo done. If the symptoms worsen, they will proceed. Concomitant medications included diltiazem for blood pressure high and atorvastatin for cholesterol, both from an unspecified date and ongoing; she has been on these medications for 30 years now. On 11Jan2021, the patient experienced facial tingling, immediate pain in arm from injection, couldn't lift her arm at all, left eye twitching, chills, nausea, no appetite, whole body ache, tired, whole body trembled, nervous. On 12Jan2021, the patient experienced back pain. The patient explained that on 11Jan2021, evening at 5:15pm, she received her first COVID 19 vaccine. The Pfizer vaccine was being given out at that time. She has shellfish and iodine allergies. So, they made her sit and wait 30 minutes after being injected. One of her daughters took her. On the drive home, a few minutes after leaving she developed facial tingling. At first, she thought nothing of it. She did have immediate pain in her arm from the injection. By the time she got home, she couldn't lift her arm at all. It was that painful. The next morning, she couldn't lift arm, and if she tried, she would be in pain. Also, her left eye started twitching right away also. That night she really noticed it. It was not a constant twitching. She thought at first it was because she was tired or from the pain in her body. But then she noticed the next day it was still doing that. It was still twitching. It is not constant, but it was here and there. She still had it on 13Jan2021, but so far nothing at the day of report (14Jan2021). She also had chills. She had on double clothes, and coverings on her feet and hands. The chills wouldn't go away. Her whole body trembled. On 13Jan2021, Wednesday morning, they went away. She experienced nausea and no appetite. Her whole body ached. It was so brutal. The problem was with her left eye. It didn't twitch constantly, but it got her nervous. She is pretty sure she is going to refuse the second dose. She has heard that the 2nd part is when most people have the worst side effects. So, she is not comfortable getting it. She also got back pain. It wasn't severe, but it was there. She is against getting the second shot. She stated that she is a medical assistant at a pediatric office. She doesn't have a prescribing doctor. She got it (vaccine) because of her age. She was advised to get it as she was around patients. Work gave them the option. The inability to move her arm ended in the middle of night at 4 am 14Jan 2021. She noticed she could move her arm. Her second dose is scheduled for 01Feb2021 at 8:45 am. She does work in a pediatric office. If the second part of side effects are worse, then she doesn't want to take the chance. The eye has her concerned. Outcome of the events were as follows: facial tingling recovered on 11Jan2021, immediate pain in arm from injection recovered on 13Jan2021, chills recovered on 13Jan2021, nausea recovered on 13Jan2021, no appetite recovered on 13Jan2021, whole body ache recovered on 13Jan2021, couldn't lift her arm at all recovered on 14Jan2021, back pain was recovering, while outcome for events left eye twitching, tired, whole body trembled, and nervous, was unknown.   Information about lot/batch number has been requested.
LAB_DATA: Test Name: echo; Result Unstructured Data: Test Result:unknown results
CUR_ILL: Iodine allergy (carries epi pen); Mitral valve prolapse (for about 20 years now. They are just watching it now.); Shellfish allergy (carries epi pen)
HISTORY: Medical History/Concurrent Conditions: Blood pressure high; Cholesterol

The patient's medical history was not provided. concomitant medications were metoprolol, clonixin lysinate, pargeverine hydrochloride, levothyroxine sodium, magnesium malate, zinc glycinate and vitamin d [vitamin d nos].   On 06 Jan 2021, the patient received their first of two planned doses of mRNA-1273 (Lot: unknown) "subcutaneously" in her right arm for prophylaxis of COVID-19 infection.  On 06 Jan 2021, the patient stated that the vaccine was applied on the lower part of the deltoid muscle. Her health care professional checked that it was done subcutaneously. She experienced redness at the injection site, bruise and an unusual lump.   On 13 Jan 2021, the patient began to experience itchiness, which was treated with diphenhydramine hydrochloride.   Action taken with mRNA-1273 in response to the event was not reported.   The outcome of the events, Redness at the injection site, bruise and injection site unusual, were considered ongoing.   The outcome of event, vaccine injected subcutaneously, was resolved 06 Jan 2021.   The outcome of the event, Itchiness, was resolved on 15 Jan 2021.; Reporter's Comments: This report refers to a case of incorrect route of product administration for mRNA-1273 and concerns a 67 year-old, female patient, who experienced the events of redness at the injection site, bruise, injection site unusual lump and itchiness. The events of redness at the injection site, bruise, injection site unusual lump occurred the same day after the first and only dose of mRNA-1273 vaccine administration. The event of itchiness occurred approximately 7 days after the first and only dose of mRNA-1273 vaccine administration. Based on the current available information and temporal association between the use of the product and the start of the events, a causal relationship cannot be excluded and the events are assessed as possibly related.

Concurrent medical conditions included memory impairment. Concomitant products included Herpes zoster (Shingrix).   On 15th October 2020, the patient received the 2nd dose of Shingrix. On 15th October 2020, unknown after receiving Shingrix and an unknown time after receiving Shingrix, the patient experienced drug dose administration interval too short. On an unknown date, the outcome of the drug dose administration interval too short was unknown.  Additional details were provided as follows: The age at vaccination was not reported. The patient with bad memory had received first dose of Shingrix on 15th September 2020 (batch number 75P7G and expiry date 17th April 2022) but the patient was not sure if she got second shot on 15th October 2020, which led to shortening of vaccination schedule. The pharmacist was looking for some guidance for the patient and also asked about what would happen if patient received a third dose of Shingrix. The reporter consented to follow up. This case was processed conservatively considering that there was shortening of vaccination schedule as it was unknown if the patient indeed received the 2nd dose.

Patient received the influenza vaccine on 12/30/2020 (unclear which version). On 1/9/2021, she presented to Hospital with 5 days of numbness, paresthesias, and weakness in both lower extremities. Neurological exam, lumbar puncture, and MRI of brain/spine were all consistent with acute inflammatory demyelinating polyneuropathy (a subset of Guillain-Barre Syndrome). She was admitted to the Neurology service, and treated with IVIG. She has been receiving physical therapy, and her strength/sensory symptoms are improving, but still significant.
LAB_DATA: Lumbar puncture (1/10/2021) with albuminocytologic dissociation (elevated protein, normal WBC) MRI brain/spine (1/9/20201):  1. Diffuse enhancement and mild thickening of the cauda equina nerve roots with a slight ventral predominance. 2. Mild enhancement of cervical dorsal/ventral nerve roots and thoracic dorsal nerve roots. 3. Avid enhancement of the CN V, CN VII/VIII, and possibly the CN IX/X complexes. 4. Pertinent negatives: - No discrete signal abnormality or enhancement of the brain parenchyma or spinal cord. - No broader pattern of leptomeningeal enhancement separate from the cranial nerves. 5. Findings are most suggest of Guillain-Barre syndrome, possibly the Miller-Fischer variant. Infectious/neoplastic meningitis (e.g. Lyme), CIDP, or Charcot-Marie-Tooth are felt to be much less likely given the clinical course, degree of nerve root thickening, and sparing of the leptomeninges.
OTHER_MEDS: Aripiprazole 2mg daily, methylphenidate 27mg daily, guanfacine 1 mg nightly

It was red and real painful; This spontaneous report was received from a consumer and refers to a female patient of unknown age. The patient was allergic to gatifloxacin (TEQUIN) and levofloxacin (LEVAQUIN). Historical drugs included gatifloxacin (TEQUIN) and levofloxacin (LEVAQUIN). Concomitant therapies included: levothyroxine (SYNTHROID) and fluticasone (FLONASE).   On 28-AUG-2020, the patient wac vaccinated with the first dose of varicella virus vaccine live (oka/merck)(VARIVAX), 0.5 ml, subcutaneously for prevention of chickenpox (lot # and expiration date were no provided). On 11-DEC-2020, patient was vaccinated with the second dose of varicella virus vaccine live (oka/merck)(VARIVAX), 0.5 ml, subcutaneously for prevention of chickenpox (lot # and expiration date were no provided). She reported having no type of reaction after first dose of varicella virus vaccine live (oka/merck)(VARIVAX), but after second dose on 11-DEC-2020, she stated that her arm completely broke out where she had the vaccine. It was red and real painful. She had oral pain that developed on 02-JAN-2021 and got much worse on 03-JAN-2021. She called her dentist on 04-JAN-2021 and was seen on 05-JAN-2021. The patient went to urgent care on 06-JAN-2021 due to the pain and was prescribed Augmentin 87 5mg , twice a day (bid). She then saw an endodontist on 07-JAN-2021 and an ear, nose, throat (ENT) physician on 08-JAN-2021. ENT felt it was shingles that attacked her trigeminal nerve. ENT physician started her on Acyclovir 1 g, three times a day (tid), prednisone 20mg and gabapentin 300mg, tid. The patient ended up in the emergency room due to severe oral pain on 09-JAN-2021. The physician at emergency room switched caller from gabapentin to carbamazepine 100mg, tid. On 11-JAN-2021, she saw another endodontist, who stated it may be shingles induced by the varicella virus vaccine live (oka/merck)(VARIVAX), that attacked her trigeminal nerve. The outcome of adverse events was reported as recovering.  The reporter considered herpes zoster to be related to varicella virus vaccine live (Oka/Merck)(VARIVAX). The causal relationship between oral pain, pain in extremity, injection site pain and injection site redness was not provided.  Upon internal review, the events of herpes zoster and oral pain were considered to be medically significant.
HISTORY: Medical History/Concurrent Conditions: Allergic reaction to antibiotics

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Received vaccine around 0900 on 25 Jan 2021.  At some time early in the morning of 26 Jan she experienced headache and felt very tired so stayed home from work. During the morning she mainly slept however had some Motrin and a banana around 0830 due to feeling feverish. She went back to sleep until about 1030. When she woke up, she still felt feverish and then noticed her pulse started racing a few minutes later. Her husband took her BP but her pulse was reading ?error?.  She then put on her iWatch and had a pulse of 210. She felt very sweaty, hot and ?weird??like she might pass out but I did not have any pain other than my throat felt tight.  She went to the ER. Within about 30-40 minutes of the onset of SVT she was given adenosine and converted with a 6mg dose.
OTHER_MEDS: Mometasone furoate, estradiol patch, singulair, zyrtec, pantoprazole, albuterol

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Not sure if she got enough of her first dose; A spontaneous report was received from a 48-year-old, female patient, who received Moderna's COVID-19 vaccine (mRNA-1273) and was not sure if she got enough of her first dose.   There were no medical history and concomitant medications provided.  On 21 Jan 2021, the patient received their first of two planned doses of mRNA-1273 (Lot number: 043L20A) intramuscularly in the left arm for prophylaxis of COVID-19 infection.   On 21 Jan 2021, during her vaccination, the needle went in and she felt poke of the needle. When the technician pulled the syringe out, some of the liquid squirted inside her windshield. The patient described it as "It was not a drop or two. It was more of a squirt that splattered and dripped down. It was more than a sprinkle of raindrop." She was not sure if she got enough of her first dose. The zero dose being the little bit of extra liquid that is left in the syringe after the vaccine." No treatment information was provided. SYMPTOM_TEXT: About 9PM after the receiving the vaccine I started had riggers which lasted for about an hour. I couldn't reach for my phone or call for help. I either passed out or fell asleep. Around 1AM I woke up and checked my temperature 102.7.  Some point after I took some Tylenol but don't remember when. I finally had to call for help from my family in the morning because I was not able to pee or drink. Tuesday was my fever was still 102.7 with taking Tylenol and Advil it would just go back up.  Tuesday I had Riggers again about 5:30 it only lasted 3-5 minutes. Wednesday my fever went down to 101.4-101.5. Have had difficulty swallowing when the fever is high, did not feel as if I had a allergic reaction or that my throat was sore it was just hard to swallow.  I have a weird bruise on my arm I have clue where I got it. I didn't urinate for 9 hours. Headache. Pulse OX was at 93-94 for Monday and Tuesday but then it came it up 95-98 yesterday.  As of today I still pretty weak no fever when I woke up.
OTHER_MEDS: Lorsartan 50 MG daily, Hydrochlorothiazide 12.5 MG,   Premarin vaginal cream 0.625 MG 3 times a week, Vitamin D,  Vitamin C, Zinc, Omega 3 with Q10, Vitamin B, Magnesium
HISTORY: problems with UTIs, Coronavirus in March in 2020 and still having long term effects.
PRIOR_VAX: yes will file a VAERS report for first dose when this one is completed.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Hot to the touch; Hives on the back; Very large, red (2.5/3in circle) allergic reaction at the injection site; Didn't feel good; Couldn't process things well; Lack of correct administration, injection appears to be lower than where normally given, was injected in the fat and not in the muscle; Swollen arm/hardness; Tired; A spontaneous report was received from a other healthcare professional, concerning a 37-year-old, female patient, who received Moderna's Covid-19 vaccine (mRNA-1273) and didn't feel good, couldn't process things well, hot to the touch, hives on the back, lack of correct administration/injection appears to be lower than where normally given/was injected in the fat and not in the muscle, swollen arm/hardness, tired and very large, red (2.5/3in circle) allergic reaction at the injection site.  No relevant medical history and concomitant medications were reported.  On 08-Jan-2021, prior to the onset of events, the patient received their first of two planned doses of mRNA-1273 (lot number: 011L20A) in the left non-dominant arm for prophylaxis of COVID-19 infection.   On 08-Jan-2020, the patient received vaccine, which was of lack of correct administration as it was injected in the fat and not in the muscle and injection which was appears to be lower than where normally given. On the same date, after administration of vaccine, the patient had experienced swollen arm (swelling), hives on the back, 2.5in red circle, didn't feel good, was tired and couldn't process things well. On 18-Jan-2021, 10 days after the administration of vaccine, the patient had developed very large-red allergic reaction at the injection site with perfect circle and was hot to the touch. Treatment for the event included paracetamol (acetaminophen) and loratadine.   Action taken with mRNA-1273 in response to the events were not provided.   The outcome of events didn't feel good, hot to the touch, hives on the back, tired and very large, red (2.5/3in circle) allergic reaction at the injection site was unknown. The event lack of correct administration, injection appears to be lower than where normally given, was injected in the fat and not in the muscle was considered to be resolved on 08-Jan-2021. The event swollen arm/hardness was considered to be resolved on 09-Jan-2021. The event couldn't process things well was considered to be resolved on 15-Jan-2021.; Reporter's Comments: This spontaneous report refers to a case of a 37-year-old female patient who experienced non-serious events of lack of correct administration/injection appears to be lower than where normally given/was injected in the fat and not in the muscle ( inappropriate route of vaccine administered), didn't feel good, couldn't process things well, hot to the touch, hives on the back, swollen arm/hardness, tired and very large, red (2.5/3in circle) allergic reaction at the injection site..  All events excluding (large-red allergic reaction at the injection site with perfect circle hot to the touch) developed on the same day after the administration of the mRNA-1273 vaccine (lot # 011L20A, expiration date-unknown). The event of large-red allergic reaction at the injection site with perfect circle which was hot to the touch developed 10 days after the vaccine administration. Based on the information provided which includes a temporal association, a causal association between the administration of the vaccine and the other reported events cannot be excluded. Tiredness, redness and hives are consistent with the safety profile of the vaccine. The event of inappropriate route of vaccine administered is considered not applicable.

Customer denies feeling SOB, difficulty breathing or tongue/throat swelling. BP 120/78, HR 71, O2 95% RA, RR 18. Lungs CTA, RRR.   Customer accepts Benadryl 50mg PO @ 0939. No rash, hives noted on exposed skin or at site of injection in left arm. Customer monitored at site. Customer aware that this provider will notify PCP Team of incident for post vaccine check in. Customer denies questions/concerns at this time. Customer released from site at 1025 ambulating independently with steady gait, no escalation of symptoms reported, no obvious s/sx of distress.

That evening when changing into pajamas, I noticed both my legs had purple blotches from above my knees down to both feet. It looked worse when I stood. As a nurse, I knew this was mottling. I have never had this in my life. I immediately took 3 baby aspirin 81 mg each. I was so exhausted, I went to bed. 01/06/21 I woke up feeling better. My scalp still itched but not as bad. My legs were still mottled from above my knees down to feet, still worse when I stood. I took 3 baby aspirin 81 mg each at 08:00. My arm still was sore but less severe. Mild headache & ache and pains in joints. The mottling in my legs has continued & improved but I notice it mostly after showering now. I reported these symptoms to my doctor. He has advised not to get second dose & to continue aspirin 81mg daily. Prior to getting the vaccine I informed the infection control nurse about my symptoms that began 12/23/20 & the negative covid test taken on 01/04/21. She recommended I take the vaccine.

At 1443 C-O reported improvement in symptoms except now had headache and drowsiness, BP 118/78, Pulse 90, oxygen saturation 98. Client received Moderna Vaccination at School Based Immunization Clinic  at 9:20AM.  Client was sent to the observation area after the shot for 30 mins due to history of severe allergy to Morphine (self reported).  At 10:05AM,  client stated to complain about a headache and feeling extremely exhausted.   Client was told by the observation team to lay head on table and team alerted PHN about client.  PHN came over to observation area to evaluate client. While PHN was talking with client, client stated she was very nervous about getting the shot, stated she didn't want to get another one, was shaking all over, said she was dizzy and them became limp.  Client was moved to the floor for evaluation.  9-1-1 was called for EMS to arrive to school clinic.  PHN took initial vitals:  B/P  158/96, Pulse 120,  Resp  44.  Client was asked to start taking slower deep breaths to help with oxygen flow.  Client started to open eyes and become more alert.  Stated again she was not going to get another COVID vaccine and that she was very nervous about getting this vaccine.  EMS arrived at 10:24AM.  Vitals were reevaluated B/P:  146/88,  Pulse: 84, Oxygen 94, Resp: 22.  Client was moved to sitting in a chair and recoperating well.  Still complained about being sleepy and headache.   Client's husband arrived to the event and when client saw husband, she started to shake and became limp again.  Client them moved to the floor again and then transferred by EMS to stretcher and transported to ER for evaluation.
LAB_DATA: Client stated bloodwork and EKG were done at the hospital, but unknown what tests were done.  Client stated she was released back to home the same day.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: The next morning after receiving the vaccine I noticed that my mother she talking to me, as her primary giver she knows me and comfortable to me. She tells me the same story over the over with isn't abnormal. It was every 3-4 words she was jumbling her words. I didn't think anything of it at first. I just let it go.   Early Wednesday morning  2:48am, I heard her in her bedroom. I went to check on her, I found at her dresser trying to put her watch on. She didn't know who was I or didn't know where she was. It took me about 40 minutes to calm her down. Now it was every 2 words that she was jumbling up. I finally got her back to bed. I went to send a message to her doctor. In the morning someone from the doctor's office called back I explained what was going on and they said get her to an ER.   I took her to the hospital 01/27/2021.  She was admitted to hospital for overnight observation.  Still not been discharged. Patient was still confused when I had to left last night, did not understand where she was at or why she had to stay there. My mother was very angry when she woke up early Wednesday is not my mom she is very lovely. One year or two years she did have a TA or mini stroke.
LAB_DATA: urine, blood and MRI all appeared to be clear. The MRI showed no new no stroke (TA), The urine and blood were both determined to be "clear"

As I took the antibiotic, the spot decreased in redness and size within 48 hours. I took 500mg keflex two times a day for 7 days. I finished the antibiotic last night. The area is not as red, but looks more like a faded bruise. I read a story about ?covid arm? from USA today this morning about similar reactions and wanted to report my experience. SYMPTOM_TEXT: The evening after I got the first dose I experienced painful muscle aches starting in my legs and progressing to the rest of my body, around 7pm. My left shoulder was a little achy, but no different than any other shot. About 30 minutes later I felt chills and felt really cold. I went to bed and tried to sleep. I woke up several times in pain. I did not take any pain meds. At 1am I went to the bathroom and felt nauseous and lightheaded. My vision got blurry and it felt like I was going to pass out, so I grabbed the towel rack and closed my eyes.  I must have blacked out for a second and lowered myself down to the floor. I came to, and I was sitting on the ground, sweating a lot. I stayed on the floor for at least 10 minutes cooling down. (I had dressed warmly and turned on my heater after the chills started). I heard ringing in my ears while I was sitting on the floor. It went away after 5 minutes. I got up and went back to bed. I woke up at 9am and felt a lot better. Some minimal soreness. No more chills.
OTHER_MEDS: A Women's Multivitamin. Supplemental vitamin C, vitamin D. Quercetin. Selenium.

0912 - patient sitting in general observation. States she suddenly felt lightheaded as if she was going to pass out. States she feels her heart is doing something and has a mechanical valve. Taken via w/c to private observation area. EMT on site in attendance. Upon further eval, states she suddenly felt cold all over and her mechanical valve did something, followed by heart racing and feeling like she was going to faint. Initial vital signs - HR 135; O2 sat 99% on room air. Color sl. pale.  0917 BP 160/100 per electronic BP machine. BP rechecked manually and auscultated per EMT at 140/90. Patient states she has her yearly cardiologist visit today at 11 am. States she had a heart echocardiogram several days ago, her INR was 2.0 per yesterday's labs.  0920 Nurse auscultated patient's heart for one minute. HR strong and regular at 90bpm - clicking noted of valve. States she had some mild days of fatigue and generally not feeling well after first dose of vaccine. States she ate breakfast and is well hydrated. Gave water.  0929 - stood without dizziness, used restroom. gait steady. States she feels much better now and declines need for ambulance.  0931 Recheck VS - BP 136/88; HR 85: RR 18; O2 99% on room air. Ambulated outside, accompanied by EMT and nurse, states she feels fine now and unsure what her heart did. Ambulated on own to personal vehicle.
HISTORY: Mechanical heart valve replaced in 2017 for birth defect - states born with a biscuspid stenotic aortic valve.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: On 01/26/21, 67 yo F with anemia, asthma, Afib (on rivaroxaban), fibromyalgia, DM2, HLD, and osteoarthritis was administered COVID-19 Moderna vaccine 0.5 mL in left deltoid (Lot #011J20A, Exp: 05/11/21). Pt has numerous documented allergies including iodine (hives, facial swelling), Shellfish Containing Products (Hives, facial swelling) and penicillin (edema). Pt initially tolerated injection without incident and was sent for post-injection observation. Within 10 minutes, pt developed acute SOB, increased WOB, wheezing, and cough. Pt also reported itching skin and scratchy throat. Provider notified and exam found pt in respiratory distress with increased work of breathing, bronchospasm and wheezing. Pt had no rash, lip swelling or vomiting. Vitals assessed as O2 sats >96%, BP 140-150s/60s, HR 70-80s. Pt was administered albuterol 2.5 mg via nebulization x 2, diphenhydramine 50 mg IM and epinephrine 0.3 mg IM. Pt was subsequently transported to ED. By time of arrival, pt's symptoms had significantly improved. Pt administered famotidine 20 mg IV and prednisone 60 mg PO and placed on continuous cardiac and pulse oximetry monitoring. After complete symptom resolution, pt was discharged in stable condition. Pt's allergy profile was updated to include Moderna Covid-19 Vaccine (eua) (rxn: Anaphylaxis; severity: High).
CUR_ILL: anemia, asthma, Afib (on rivaroxaban), fibromyalgia, DM2, HLD, and osteoarthritis

PCP recommended patient sees an allergist for further investigation and refrain from second dose of vaccine

SYMPTOM_TEXT: First 2 days after vaccination, I had some injection site pain that was improving. Day 5 after vaccination, I developed lymphadenopathy on my left side with swelling into the chest area developing on day 6. Day 8 after vaccination, my injection site turned red and itchy and I began to have trouble breathing. I went to urgent care.  I saw P. A. She said that it was more likely that the difficulty breathing would be due to my asthma, but she could not recommend whether or not I should receive my second dose. She proscribed 20mg of Prednisone and refilled my albuterol prescription. About 20 hours later, my breathing is still difficult and my arm still itches.  We also discussed that the respiratory symptoms could be caused or exasperated by COVID-19, so I am waiting on results from a covid test.
HISTORY: Asthma that has not needed treatment in 7 years. Scoliosis

fever; chills; severe headache; severe muscle and joint pain; chest tightness; mild nausea; lungs felt inflamed, making it difficult to take deep breaths; unable to sleep; severe muscle and joint pain; This is a spontaneous report from a contactable health care professional (patient).  A 29-year-old female patient recived the second dose of BNT162B2 (Pfizer-BioNTech COVID-19 vaccine, lot no: EK4176) via an unspecified route of administration on 12Jan2021 at 08:45 at a single dose on the left arm for COVID-19 immunization. The patient's medical history was not reported. The patient had no known allergies.  Concomitant medication included colecalciferol (VITAMIN D [COLECALCIFEROL], manufacturer unknown), vitamin B12 (manufacturer unknown), vitamin c  (manufacturer unknown), melatonin (manufacturer unknown), biotin (manufacturer unknown) and elderberry [sambucus nigra] (manufacturer unknown). The patient received the first dose of BNT162B2 (Pfizer-BioNTech COVID-19 vaccine, lot no: EJ1685) on 22Dec2020 at 9:00 PM on the left arm. The patient did not receive other vaccines in four weeks. The patient reported that after her second dose, she began experiencing severe side effects around 5:00 pm the same day (about 7 hours after the dose was administered). These side effects were fever, chills, severe headache, severe muscle and joint pain, chest tightness, and mild nausea. She also added a difficult symptom to describe, but her lungs felt inflamed, making it difficult to take deep breaths. These symptoms lasted for 36 hours unabated, and she was unable to sleep, go to work, eat, or go about daily activities during this time. After 36 hours, the fever, chills, headache, and nausea subsided, but the muscle and joint pain and chest tightness persisted. Pfizer BioNTech Covid 19 vaccine = treatment under Emergency Use Authorization(EUA): Patient presented to Covid Vaccine Clinic. Appointment time was 0925. Patient indicated she did have allergies on her screening sheet. Pfizer- BioNTech Covid-19 vaccine (0.3ml) was administered per protocol (Lot # EL3246, exp. date 04/30/21). At 0947 I was asked to come assess patient by the monitor. Patient reported her tongue felt thick and the roof of her mouth felt weird. I asked if her throat felt tight, if she had any shortness of breath or chest tightness. She denied any other symptoms. I asked if she had any allergies. Patient reported having a reaction in the past to adhesive from EKG leads, codeine, and contrast dye. I asked patient to pull her mask down. No swelling was observed around her mouth, lips, or tongue at that time. No hives were observed on her arms, chest or back. Patient than started to complain of feeling worse and had some tightness in her chest. At that time I escorted patient to a cot and advised I was going to administer an epi-pen. Patient verbalized understanding. I advised staff to call 911. At 0955 0.3 mg of epinephrine was administered into her left anteriolateral thigh. HR was 88 bpm at this time. Patient reported feeling shaky and felt like her heart was racing. I advised her that was a normal reaction to the epinephrine. Symptoms at this time did not progress. Patient reported her chest felt less tight at 10:05. EMS arrived and reported on 02 sat of 97% on room air. Patient was transported to the ED without further incident on location. Husband was present at all times and informed on all action taken.
ALLERGIES: Allergy to adhesives (rash), codeine (itching), erythromycin base (rash), iodinated contrast media (anaphylaxis), latex (rash), metoclopramide hcl (anxiety), oxycodone (rash), tetracycline (rash)

Patient lives in a SNF and received the first dose of the COVID-19 vaccine 1 day prior to admission. After the vaccine, patient had multiple rounds of vomiting. The next morning, patient was sent to emergency department for continued vomiting. On assessment, patient was found to have right sided opacities on chest x-ray. Patient was afebrile, with a normal WBC, and had mild increase in his chronic oxygen requirement. It was thought that these right sided opacities could be aspiration pneumonitis/pneumonia from the recurrent vomiting in a bed bound SNF patient. Vomiting leading to aspiration pneumonitis/pneumonia. Idiosyncratic response not expected from normal pharmacological mode of action (MOA) vomiting post vaccine leading to aspiration. Vomiting does appear to be linked to receipt of vaccine given timing. Of note, patient had COVID-19 requiring hospital admission approximately 1 month before receiving the COVID-19 vaccine. It is possible that the recent COVID-19 infection contributed to a worsened response to the COVID-19 vaccine.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Severe Left Leg, Hip and Lower left leg pain (Sciatic Nerve) it appears the vaccine may have irritated sciatic nerve pain.  Left left leg numbness.  Decreased mobility, difficulty sitting, walking, and even lying in bed.  Started very quickly without andy known injury.  Pain continued to worsen.  Pain even worse after second injection.  Now two weeks after second shot, the pain is going away.  It is like the nerve irritation is subsiding.  The way the irritation is subsiding makes it seem that the vaccination may have caused irritation to the nerve. After receiving 1st and continuing through the second vaccine, started having severe sciatica pain going down left hip and leg.  Left leg pain and numbness.  Thought I had done something to damage the nerve.  Hurt to sit, hurt to stand and even hurt when in bed. The pain was so severe it caused issues with any mobility.  Took Advil, Aspiring, Tylenol and nothing helped.  Received second vaccine 1/12/2021 the pain continued and even got worse.  It was to the point I couldn't even walk.  I couldn't figure out how I had damaged the nerve.  I am now thinking it was from the vaccine.  I believe the vaccine irritated the nerve.  The nerve pain is starting to go away.  Normally if you  have a sciatic nerve issue, it just doesn't go away on its own.  I know there have been reports of severe back and neck pain.  I believe it can irritate the nerves which cause severe pain.  I wanted this reported in cases others complain of similar issues.  The good thing it is improving.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: On day one (9 FEB 2021) of my injection, I developed a red swelling at the injection site, a headache, fatigue, and swollen, tender arm.  By the next morning, day 2, I had a dime size bruise from the injection and the arm tissue was swollen and hard.  The swelling last 4 days.  The bruise lasted 12 days.   On the 7th day after (16 JAN 2021) receiving the Moderna COVID-19 injection in my left arm, I developed a red, puffy, bumpy rash on my arm, around where the injection was given.  It appeared after a routine shower, without any new use of products.  It was initially about 3 inches wide by 4 inches long, and almost crescent shaped.  We monitored the rash, as it increased in size over the next two days, growing to 4.5 inches wide by 6 inches long. The rash remained red, puffy, and bumpy during.  It never itched or wept any fluid.  Then on the 4th day of the rash, it turned light pink and diminished in color and area throughout the day, however, it was circled by a red ring outlining the rash.  The rash was still faintly visible on the 5th day and completely gone by the 6th day.  We also noticed it felt very hot to the touch and took the temperature of the site.  It peaked at 104 degrees Fahrenheit, while my head and neck temperatures peaked at 101 degrees Fahrenheit.

In September 2015, my son started having significant sleep issues which progressed and got worse as time went on. It got to the point he physically COULD NOT fall asleep. During the transition from "awake" to "sleep" he started to have severe epileptic episodes.  The epileptic episodes would go on all night from approx 11p until approx 6a. ONLY occuring when his brain started to wander off to sleep. He got to the point where he couldnt even get 4 solid hours of sleep in a night. I of course brought him to his pediatrician. They had zero answers in anyway shape or form and referred us to a pediatric neurologist who also determined there was "nothing" wrong w/ my son. We were also referred to an ENT Dr who referred us for a sleep study.  This went on for approx 10mos, at which point I realized none of the drs were able to give me any explanantion what so ever. I started researching my sons symptoms. Nothing seemed to fit. The only thread of info I could find where the exact symptoms of my son matched was in a forum that different moms had written in. They also had been left in the dark and had no answer about what was happening to their kids. Upon relentless research, I ordered lavender,vetiver, and cedarwood essential oils. I applied at night before bed and for THE FIRST time in almost a year my sons epuleptic episodes went from a 10, to about a 4. At that point I cancelled all appointments related to his condition bc I was better able to treat my son then any of the Drs had been able to.
LAB_DATA: Blood tests, and EEG which indicated a firing in his left lobe (the part that controls muscle movements) was out of control. All blood tests came back normal.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Patient came to receive dose 2 of Covid19 Moderna vaccine. States 1 hour after the first dose (administered on  12/28/20) she was at work and her blood pressure dropped, she became dizzy and her face went white. She said her mother insisted she go to the ER to be examined. She states upon examination she was given fluids and tests were ran and the ER staff said she was fine. Explained this to physician at vaccine site and she said it was not a contraindication to receive 2nd dose and it sounds like possible vasovagal reaction or hypoglycemia. Patient states she still wanted to receive vaccine.  Was instructed to monitor patient for 30 minutes after vaccination,  assist patient in ambulation to waiting area to lower fall risk and provided patient with apple juice and trail mix in case of possible hypoglycemia.  About 5-10 minutes after vaccine, patient stated she became dizzy and was dry heaving. She was assisted to supine position; vitals were taken and blood pressure was slightly elevated. 911 was called. Before arrival of EMS, patient stated she was feeling better and vital signs stable. Patient was helped to ambulate around waiting area and upon arrival of EMS, patient states she did not need to be transported. Patient was observed for about 20-25 more minutes and she was fully recovered. Spoke with Dr who was on scene after the incident and she believes it was anxiety.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: The HCW noted w/i 1 hr of vaccination a constellation of symptoms including dizziness, disorientation, and fatigue; and by 4 hrs she developed swelling LUE with pain and some swelling extending to the L neck.  Over the next several days she reported marked swelling and tenderness over the triceps upper arm area; persistent swelling and pain in the neck that required cold packs for a couple days.  The reaction appeared to be more pronounced and extensive akin to the Humira local reaction she would ordinarily get; the last dose of that was 4 months prior.  By history, it sounds like extensive angioedema.  At no point was there any pruritus, erythema, or hive or rash on any other part of the body; no respiratory compromise, stridor or wheeze; and no fever.  Symptoms subsided over several days and she was well on day of her presenting for her second vaccination.  The vaccinator (who is a pediatrician), an on-call allergist; and this reporter (a medical oncologist) all consulted on best approach.  The allergist recommends skin testing; Humira may have a polysorbate component; and we collectively thought a contraindication to proceeding.  Given the deliberation the HCW actually elected also not to proceed.  We informed her that early data suggests one dose of the Moderna vaccine may confer an approximate 80% protection.  She will present to EHS for further evaluation.
HISTORY: As above - hydroadenitis suppurtiva; and PTSD after service in Iraq.
ALLERGIES: Extensive h/o hydroadenitis suppurtiva and brisk skin reactions

Patient delivered a baby girl at 35+6 wks via c-section for placenta previa. She delivered at Hospital. The female child  was taken to the (hospital) NICU due to prematurity and myelomenigocele (subsequently repaired).   Pattient was vaccinated on 12/12/20 for varicella (2 days postpartum). Patient visited NICU and breastfed/ held her infant daily.  Female Child (FC) required prolonged NICU stay due to hydrocephalus requiring VP shunt placement on 12/16/20 and infection of VP shunt with staph epidermidis on 1/1/21 which was successfully treated with vancomycin.   As she was being prepared for discharge on 1/12/21, FC was noted to have multiple vesicular lesions throughout legs, trunk and arms,  concerning for varicella. On 1/13/21 PCR testing done both  on serum sample and swabs of lesions which resulted positive for varicella.  FC and other infants in surrounding area of NICU were placed on airborne precautions. FC was started on acyclovir. Other infants were given prophylaxis varicella Immunoglobulin as they were considered potentially exposed. After consultation with MERCK, swabs of the lesions were sent to a separate lab to determine if the varicella strain was wild type or Oka (vaccine) strain. The results came back positive for Oka (vaccine) strain. FC only exhibited cutaneous symptoms and recovered completely. Her hospitalization was prolonged due to varicella and she was discharged on 1/20/21
LAB_DATA: 1/13/21: Infant's cutaneous lesions positive for Varicella by PCR. Notified MERCK and sent swabs to designated lab for strain identification 1/13/21: Varicella viral serum level: >116,000 copy/mL 1/14/21: Results from cutaneous lesions positive for Oka (vaccine) strain varicella virus

I noticed on Day 3 after shot that my arm was increasingly red and tender with a hot red bump at the injection site. By day 7 the injection site had swelled to more than three times its size and became even more painful itchy and red. By Saturday the 9th day the size of the injection site had taken over the majority of the upper part of my arm. At that point I decided I needed urgent Care. I was seen by a doctor who said she had similar reactions but once she felt the heat coming from my arm she placed me on Doxycycline, Zyrtec, and Benadryl. After using the new medicines for 2 days the spot on my arm grew even more and became an irregular shape. Once I saw the irregular shape and continued swelling I made an appointment to see my regular family doctor. My doctor decided to put me on the antibiotic Keflex in addition to the Doxycycline, Zyrtec, and Benadryl. I am now at day 14 since the injection, I am continuing all Keflex, Doxycycline, Zyrtec, Benadryl, and I am still experiencing some discomfort and itching. My doctor gave me the option to use steroids but the swelling and redness has gone away so we are going to hold off for now. If symptoms persist we will seek blood tests.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Woke up Sunday morning around 0700 1-24-2021 after had receiving my 2nd dose of the vaccine the day prior and was feeling all the normal muscle aches, pain and fatigue. The site where the swelling was located was very sensitive to the slightest touch, also on the same arm I received the injection. About 2 hours after waking, I started experiencing dizziness and nausea very suddenly to the point where I had to sit myself down in the hall way for a few minutes. I thought at one point I needed to call an ambulance as I made my way to lay down on my couch because I felt so sick. With in about 15 minutes after laying still on the couch the overwhelming need to vomit came over me. Which I did do for a good 5 minutes. There was quite a bit of relief from the nausea and dizziness shortly after but remained present the entire day. However the severe head ache continued until the morning of 1-27 and the lymph node still is slightly swollen with sensitivity to the touch.
Had  sudden onset of vertigo with severe symptoms the first two days that decreased in severity over the course of a week, that began  three days after being vaccinated.

However, this Monday (day 7) I had what felt like a mosquito bite at or near the injection site and it itched quite badly that night. Yesterday (day 8) I didn?t notice much, but last night it started to itch again and I noticed that it had developed into more of a rash around the injection site (nowhere else). It was pink and somewhat warm. I put ice on it and took a Tylenol and it was much improved and it hasn?t bothered me much since then. It is calmer today, but still pink.  I am not really concerned about this, but I thought I should let you know just in case there is something else I should know or do. I plan to go ahead with my second dose which is scheduled for 2/15.

The evening that I received the vaccine, I  started having some numbness in my hands. The following morning, I continued to have numbness in my hands but also in my face. By the evening , the day after I had received the vaccine, I felt like my swallowing was slightly impaired and I went to urgent care. I was able to complete all neurological tests and given a prescription for hydroxyzine, thinking that I may have had a slight histamine response.  I slept approximately 10 hours that night and then fell asleep again from 8:30-11:30 this morning due to high levels of fatigue. Today (~54 hours later), the numbness in my hands and face seems to be getting slightly worse.  I also feel some generalized weakness. I'm still able to do normal day to day activities but it feels abnormal.
LAB_DATA: I passed a neurological screen  at urgent care last night. I did have an elevated heart rate and high blood pressure but I was also extremely anxious about what was happening to me. No further testing or lab results were completed.
OTHER_MEDS: No medications taken at the time of the  vaccination.

Rapid heart beat around 3 o?clock in the morning woke me with symptoms of the feeling that my heart was in my throat. My face felt flushed. I was able to monitor my heart rate and temperature but was not able to rest well for several hours. I had a doctor?s appointment at 8 o?clock the next morning and reported the symptoms to him. SYMPTOM_TEXT: Moderna COVID?19 Vaccine EUA  About 8 hours after the shot, I had chills and developed swelling on the right side of my upper lip. In the morning the swelling and chills were gone, and I had a really stiff upper shoulder and up to my neck. I feel totally fine the next morning, but concerned about a worse reaction to the second shot.

The evening I received the 2nd dose of Moderna (1/24) I started having a headache followed by fever, chills,  arm soreness, and fatigue. Monday, 1/25, I no longer had headache but fever, chills, arm soreness, and fatigue was still present.  I felt so cold I had on long sleeves and multiple blankets. I took tylenol for my symptoms. This latest until Tuesday morning  (1/26) when I awoke when all of my symptoms were gone other than my arm in discomfort. When I looked into the mirror I saw  a red welty rash on my arm. I  continued to take tylenol and iced my arm. I called my primary care doctor. I later received a message from her office to take tylenol and ice arm and come in to be seen if my arm did not improve. Later on in the evening the size of the rash continued to grow and get angry red. I felt great pain. I ended up going to the ER to get it looked it. I was given a rx for keflex to treat my arm for potential cellulitis of the arm but also noted that what I was experiencing was likely a localized reaction to the injection itself per the discharge summary. That evening I circled the rash so I could keep track of its growth. It did slightly grow the next day (1/27).  I followed up with my primary care doctor today (1/28) as I was instructed by my ER discharge summary to follow up in 3 days and she only had availability 2 days later.  The rash appears to finally have stopped growing but it still present. It does appear to have faded some. I was advised to take Claritin or Allegra and use calamine lotion.

She had a nurse check her blood pressure and it was 101/65 and her heart rate was 138 bpm.  She felt presyncopal so she went to the ED for evaluation.  By the time she got to the ED, she felt her throat was scratchy, and when she would lie down flat she felt her throat was occluding.  She notes that she is s/p tonsillectomy in 12-2020, and considered whether that was playing a role in her symptoms, but she had not had any of those throat symptoms for 1 week prior to getting her COVID-19 vaccine. About 13 minutes after the injection, the patient walked back to the nurse's station, stating that he did not feel good.  He was pale and clammy and started to fall.  He was sat in the chair, and he started to lose consciousness.  Pulse was faint and the blood pressure was initially 61, pulse about 60.  He has no skin rash, stridor, respiratory distress.  Respiration was regular and unlabored.  Within 10 minutes, he opens his eyes and started responding, his blood pressure improved to 110-120's, pulses 60's, O2 sat 98%, unlabored breathing.  He was transferred to a wheelchair and laid down on the exam table.  He was observed for another 30 minutes.  His vital signs remained stable.  He is able to drink water and able to walk around in his own power without difficulty.   The patient stated that he does not like needles, and he has not had any vaccination for a long time.   Impression: Vasovagal syncope Adverse reaction to the SARS-CoV-2 vaccine, not anaphylactic reaction.

28 January 2021  To : Vaccine Adverse Event Reporting SystemO  Im am writing to report a possible adverse reaction . On Wednesday, January 20, 2021, at 9:22 AM, I received my first dose vaccination of Pfizer COVID-19 Lot# EL3247 at the Health Clinic Site.  At approximately 4 PM that afternoon I experienced the first of a number of episodes of watery, gassy, non - bloody diarrhea which was heralded by great urgency but was accompanied by neither  fever, abdominal pain , nor any other systemic signs or symptoms.  There was no anosmia, headache, nor respiratory difficulty.  I continued to feel clinically well and I had no change of my daily activities.  I experienced no change of appetite.  I experienced two or three such urgent episodes daily for the next eight days. At no time during that week did I have a formed stool.  I cannot recall the last prior episode of watery . gassy diarrhea since it is not an experience which I have experience for, likely, decades.  During the 7-8 day period, my wife and I ate exactly the same foods. My wife experienced no diarrhea, cramping of frequent stooling. She reports that all of her stools have been normal. After three or four days, I spoke with several internists who suggested that I obtain a   SARS-CO-V-2 NAT, NP Swab test. Since I had been symptomatic for a number of days. I self quarantined and moved out of my wife?s and my bedroom. During all that time I wore a face mask and increased the frequency and duration of hand washing. NO SARS-CoV-2 RNA was detected by PCR.  It is now 48 hours since my last watery, gassy stool. I have just passed a normal appearing, non -melanotic, formed stool.  Sincerely,  Patient
LAB_DATA: SARS-COV-2 NAT, NO SWAB, Symptomatic  No SARS-CoV-2 RNA Detected by PCR
OTHER_MEDS: lisinopril 2.5 mg q hs        atorvastatin 10 mg q hs
